item.title: [HIVE-19110] Vectorization: Enabling vectorization causes TestContribCliDriver udf_example_arraymapstruct.q to produce Wrong Results
item.description: Found in vectorization enable by default experiment.
item.summary: Vectorization: Enabling vectorization causes TestContribCliDriver udf_example_arraymapstruct.q to produce Wrong Results

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
There are several issues related to this bug. And they are all related to VectorExpressionWriter for List, Map and Struct in the java file VectorExpressionWriterFactory.

  1. For List, null values is not handled properly.
  2. For Map, the VectorExpressionWriter is not implemented for Map.
  3. For Struct, null values are not checked before get into struct fields.

Patch submitted with the fixes mentioned above and additional tests:

  1. Add unit test for List and Map VectorExpressionWriter. Struct has unit test for it already.
  2. Add a vectorized version of the qtest in this bug.
